snippet.textDisplay:
Knowing I like puzzles, my friends bought me one for Christmas. In a small paper bag, they handed me a pile of wooden, crooked and almost identical looking pieces of a puzzle I had never seen before and poured them to my lap.


Me: Aaaaww thank you! //starts fiddling with the pieces
Friends: You're welcome. Have fun and-
Me: So these make a cube, right? =)
Friends: Wait, WHAT? HOW did you know that?
Me: Huh? o.o I looked at the pieces?
Friends: How on Earth can you tell from those pieces that it's a cube?!
Me: I... Well... judging by the shapes I... //slips two pieces together
Friends: HUH?! That's too fast! That was luck wasn't it?
Me: No, they looked like they might fit so...
Friends: That's it, we're stepping up the game next year.


Chris, your influence has thus reached my friends. My puzzle solving skills have increased by watching your videos. I may be a novice, but in 2020 I intend to put my skills in good use by making escape rooms and treasure hunts for my friends and by DMing a D&D campaign. Thank you for increasing my confidence in creativity. And happy new year. ^^
